<br>
1) If you attempt to DC a mob that is too high do you get a message telling you so? <br>
<br>
2) If it is to high does it &quot;waste&quot; your DC ability and are you then required to wait for the ability to refresh.  If that is so this would be completely worthless to my Enchanter as he is now hunting in zones where mobs range in level from below the DC level limit to above it so it is likely that some of the same mob types will be and some won't be charmable.<br>
<br>
3) If you fail to DC does it cause aggro?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any insights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=summerlilywintermystic>Summerlily Wintermystic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(2/5/04 10:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dire Charm Question</span><hr size=1> To the best of my knowledge, <br>
<br>
1. you dont fail DC casts<br>
<br>
2. Only certain mobs can be DC'd in the planes,<br>
    Mephit Lackey's in SolRo<br>
    rusted mail and a frog, at the GY in PoV<br>
    little gnome guy at ZI in PoT<br>
just to name a few, anyways, they all are going to con LB to ya, or they do to me at 65<br>
<br>
thats about all I know, hope it helps, and adding a DC mob to any group or duo, adds a fair amount of DPS to your killing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
