<br>
1) You get a message saying that the target was to high for your dominating gaze spell.  <br>
<br>
2) You can immediately use your DC spell again after a failure due to level.  The macro recycles. <br>
<br>
3) You definately get aggro if it fails.  A good way to test it is to pacify everything, mez the mob if it is mezzable then cast the DC, if it lands then when mez drops they are all yours... if not you already have the situation under control. <br>
<br>
Hope this helps.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325693">Amberine, 65 Coercer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arbrelax>Arbrelax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(2/12/04 10:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Thanks for Info</span><hr size=1> Thank for all the responses - My Enchanter is now having great fun with Dire Charm, now only wish I had gotten it sooner. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arbrelax>Arbrelax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(3/13/04 11:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks for Info</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure if this was a change but this was in the patch message from the 3/10 Patch:<br>
<br>
Dire Charm will no longer reset after being resisted as the ability was successfully initiated.<br>
<br>
Dire Charm should now reset when used on an NPC that is too high in level.<br>
<br>
It sounds like the first part MAY be a change for the worse.  Amberine notes that you do get aggro if the DC fails due to a resist on a mob that is the correct level (i.e. failed not because the mob was too high).  I think I had noticed that also - but I think also that the ability did reset immediately.  <br>
<br>
For NPC's that were too high I recall getting a message that it didn't work but don't recall if it created aggro or if the message was simply like the ones you get when you try to cast an inappropriate spell (such as a druid &quot;animal only&quot; spell on a monster).  Anyone tried this post patch who can update us on current status:<br>
<br>
1) When resisted by a level appropriate mob you now apparently both get aggro AND have to wait for the timer to recycle before trying again?<br>
<br>
2) When you attempt to cast on a mob of too high a level - you should not lose the ability (i.e. it will be immediately available again) - - - but does it create aggro?  or do you just get a message indicating the mob is too high to be dire charmed and it is otherwise unaffected and does not even notice you or aggro on you?<br>
<br>
While I can see the &quot;logic&quot; of saying that the &quot;ability was successfully initiated&quot; and therefore it was cast and therefore the idea is that the &quot;spell itself can only be used&quot; once every recycle time.  I think however, that as you apparently get aggro from unsuccessful casts on level appropriate mobs that should be penalty enough and for game play it should be geared to one Successful DC per time period.<br>
<br>
Along those lines does anyone know of any other AA Abilities that have similar consequences?  For example, when casting an MGB - if the spell happens to fizzle does that use up the MGB ability?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any input. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showPrevMessage?topicID=341.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showNextMessage?topicID=341.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=341.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.threadControl?topicID=341.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=341.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=341.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub136.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqenchantersrealmfrm11">General<option value="eqenchantersrealmadminnotices">Admin Notices<opti